---
// input: siteConfig data, related guides list layout component
// output: Rebirth guide page showing rebirth timing strategies and post-reset rebuild routes
// pos: src/pages/rebirth.astro (更新规则：文件变更需同步本注释与所属目录 README)

import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGuides from "../components/RelatedGuides.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/config";
---

<SiteLayout title="Merge a Nuke Guide Rebirth | Roblox Tycoon Multiplier" description="Optimize rebirth cycles with the Merge a Nuke guide rebirth tips. Learn when to reset your tycoon base and quickly rebuild passive cash multipliers.">
  <main class="content-page">
    <section class="prose-block" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Rebirth guide</p>
      <h1>{siteConfig.gameName} Rebirth Guide</h1>
      <p>Rebirthing is the ultimate progression mechanism in Roblox Merge a Nuke. While doing a rebirth resets your active cash and missile levels, it rewards you with permanent stats multipliers. These multipliers allow you to spawn higher starting weapon tiers and reach late-game milestones rapidly.</p>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(18, 22, 32, 0.65); border: 1.5px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--radius-interactive); line-height: 1.6;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 8px;">Rebirth Strategy Rationale</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Rebirthing too early slows down your momentum, while rebirthing too late wastes valuable time. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> is designed to help you analyze your progression curve, identify the optimal rebirth threshold, and rebuild your nuclear base quickly after the reset.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Video Guide: Rebirth Mechanics & Timing</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.6;">Curious about how rebirth resets your base and what multipliers you get? Watch this gameplay walkthrough to learn when is the best time to execute a rebirth and how to fast-track your progression afterwards.</p>
      <div style="margin: 24px 0; max-width: 800px; aspect-ratio: 16/9; width: 100%;">
        <iframe 
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KG_lFaKZW1o" 
          title="Merge a Nuke Rebirth Strategy Video Guide" 
          frameborder="0" 
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" 
          allowfullscreen
          style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-card); border: 1px solid var(--line);"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="rebirth-timing" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Optimal timing</p>
      <h2 id="rebirth-timing" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Rebirth strategy and timing</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.6;">A successful rebirth requires careful planning. If you trigger the reset immediately after hitting the minimum cash requirement, you will struggle to rebuild early-game tiers. Follow these strategic guidelines to optimize your rebirth cycles.</p>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Finding the optimal multiplier gap</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Do not rush your rebirth. Wait until your active progression cash rate stalls and hangar upgrades feel too expensive to purchase. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> recommends checking the permanent multiplier boost offered by the rebirth prompt. If the new multiplier does not double your current speed, continue merging.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Scouting other players can also help: if server opponents are raiding you with high-tier weapons that you cannot match, rebirthing is the fastest way to bridge the level gap. Rebirth when the permanent boost is large enough to quickly surpass your old peak.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Preparing the board before resetting</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Before confirming the rebirth prompt, spend every dollar of your liquid cash on upgrades. Rebirthing resets your cash balance to zero, so saving currency is pointless. Spend all remaining cash on permanent attributes, such as spawn speed and base lock duration, which persist through resets.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Additionally, keep copyable gift codes ready. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> codes watchlist is a powerful tool to jumpstart your post-reset run. Entering promo codes immediately after a rebirth provides liquid cash to purchase upgrades instantly, bypassing early-game lag.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section" aria-labelledby="post-rebirth" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Post-reset</p>
        <h2 id="post-rebirth">Post-rebirth acceleration route</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Spawning advanced starting bombs</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">The most powerful benefit of rebirthing is the ability to bypass early merging tiers. High rebirth multipliers allow you to purchase upgrades that spawn tier-2 or tier-3 missiles directly from the incubator. This eliminates the need to merge hundreds of tier-1 duplicates.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> strategy focus is to prioritize spawn tier upgrades immediately after rebirthing. Spawning advanced bombs directly keeps your grid workspace clean, letting you rebuild your active hangar slots and cash flow in minutes.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Direct spawning of higher-tier missiles completely skips tedious early-game matching steps.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Compounding permanent tycoon yields</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Each rebirth permanently multiplies your base income rates. This compounding effect makes every subsequent merge chain more rewarding. A weapon that generated small profits in your first run becomes a massive cash generator after multiple rebirths.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">By focusing on the compounding nature of the rebirth system, you ensure that your base progression stays optimal. Use this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> roadmap to plan your resets, compound your passive income, and build the ultimate atomic tycoon base.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Compounding multipliers ensure that your cash generation speed scales to late-game levels rapidly.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section faq-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 32px; color: var(--color-yellow); font-family: var(--font-display);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div style="display: grid; gap: 24px;">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. When is the best time to perform a rebirth?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. You should trigger a rebirth when your cash flow stagnation makes purchasing the next spawn or capacity upgrade feel extremely slow. Rebirthing at this point instantly boosts your passive multiplier speed.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. What do I keep after a Rebirth in Merge a Nuke?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. You will keep your permanent upgrades, active base lock shield status, and your new permanent money multipliers. However, your pocket cash, conventional missiles on the grid, and basic spawner parameters will be reset.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. How do Rebirth multipliers affect my new run?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. Rebirth multipliers compound your passive base income. This allows you to generate cash exponentially faster in your next session. You will be able to buy spawn tier upgrades immediately, letting you skip early-game merging steps entirely.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedGuides currentSlug="rebirth" />
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
